race.description: Bwa Accountants & Business Advisors Mdn Plate
race.comment: The well-bred ALWAYS YOURS (9) - by Dundeel out of a half to Super Seth - was well-fancied on debut but got a long way back and just had too much work to do. She probably did well to only be beaten 1.6 lengths. With that under the belt, from a good gate, up in trip, she can break through here. SERENE DEFENSE (7) is another who will appreciate this trip and should be nearing peak fitness after two runs back, including a narrow second placing at the latest. COLT FORTY FIVE (2) did beat home ALWAYS YOURS last start and while he's unlikely to enjoy the position-in-running advantage over that rival that he did last start, he's not far off a win. THE TORONADO KID (8) was never a factor first-up but the trials prior were excellent and this distance is more up his alley. PRINCE MAGNETITE (6) might be ready to show something after a couple of runs back over 1200m.
